TITLE: Defining Layers in UnoCSS Rules
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to assign layers to UnoCSS rules. Rules can be assigned to a specific layer using the metadata object as the third parameter, with rules defaulting to the 'default' layer when unspecified.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unocss/unocss/blob/main/docs/config/layers.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
rules: [
  [/^m-(\d)$/, ([, d]) => ({ margin: `${d / 4}rem` }), { layer: 'utilities' }],
  // when you omit the layer, it will be `default`
  ['btn', { padding: '4px' }],
]
```

