TITLE: Creating Static Class Combinations for Dynamic Usage
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript example shows how to work around the limitation of dynamically constructed utilities by creating an object that statically lists all possible combinations of class names that might be used dynamically.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unocss/unocss/blob/main/docs/guide/extracting.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
// Since they are static, UnoCSS will able to extract them on build time
const classes = {
  red: 'text-red border-red',
  green: 'text-green border-green',
  blue: 'text-blue border-blue',
}
```

